cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the optimization of sequence-to-sequence models, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as machine translation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of stochastic computation graphs, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and optimization problems, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper proposes a reformulation of the optimization task, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The examples given in the paper are related to machine translation, which is a subfield of NLP and falls under the category of cs.CL. Finally, the paper could also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE) due to the use of deep learning techniques in sequence-to-sequence models.
